article_title: Haslam didn't violate privacy rules by releasing lawmakers' health data, AG says

article_metadata.description: Tennessee Attorney General Herbert Slatery says in a new legal opinion that Republican Gov. Bill Haslam's administration didn't violate federal privacy rules by publicly releasing the names and related information of state lawmakers who are on the state's health insurance program.
